{"id": "EUVD-2025-11249", "enisaUuid": "aed91ec0-8bfc-3063-88dd-5766d09999a1", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nLoongArch: Increase ARCH_DMA_MINALIGN up to 16\n\nARCH_DMA_MINALIGN is 1 by default, but some LoongArch-specific devices\n(such as APBDMA) require 16 bytes alignment. When the data buffer length\nis too small, the hardware may make an error writing cacheline. Thus, it\nis dangerous to allocate a small memory buffer for DMA. It's always safe\nto define ARCH_DMA_MINALIGN as L1_CACHE_BYTES but unnecessary (kmalloc()\nneed small memory objects). Therefore, just increase it to 16.", "datePublished": "2025-04-16T14:12:08", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-03T19:41:31", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-22049", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1d0def2d1658666ec1f32c9495df60e7411e3c82", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/279ec25c2df49fba1cd9488f2ddd045d9cb2112e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4103cfe9dcb88010ae4911d3ff417457d1b6a720", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8b82aea3666f8f2c78f86148d78aea99c46e0f82", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/bfff341cac7c650e6ca8d10503725992f5564d0f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f39af67f03b564b763b06e44cb960c10a382d54a", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/05/msg00045.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-22049", "GHSA-q8p5-jh8j-ww29"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "00860ff7-19d5-336d-8cf0-eb15888a5d75", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "01091ecf-5d0c-30e8-b886-6384f3b7219c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.19"}, {"id": "0cbaaabd-3981-350d-99f0-d8400e16da51", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "fa96b57c149061f71a70bd6582d995f6424fbbf4 <bfff341cac7c650e6ca8d10503725992f5564d0f"}, {"id": "16e723dc-7a4b-38fc-b1bf-3040b615dfc4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <279ec25c2df49fba1c